Great news sports fans! With the latest app update you can now record by selecting your favorite team so you ll never miss a game again. View live updates of scores and game times throughout the sports experience. Have you noticed Auto Extend displayed when you set your favorite sports event for recording This is our Automatic Recording Extension feature that will intuitively extend the recording of your event even past its scheduled airtime. You can now rest easy knowing you ll be able to watch the end of last night s game or the overtime win from your favorite team without the fear of missing out!!

We re setting the table for the holiday season by making some improvements to get you the app experience you deserve! IMPROVEMENTS: We re debuting a sleek new look for the filter and sort functionality in the Guide as well as adding a Recent Channels filter to make it easier to get to all your favorite networks. Get your TV together and update today!

Get the app experience you deserve. Check out the improvements we ve made just for you! Improvements We have improved iOS picture in picture experience making transitions between PIP and the app more seamless Searching for channels has never been easier! There are now channel numbers in your Guide that you can sort alphabetically or by number. The channel numbers will group subjects like news sports and premiums together to make it easy to find what you are looking for. We have now enabled thumbnail previews when you fast forward or rewind your recorded content
Improvements: A more seamless experience when casting for Chromecast users
We are constantly working to enhance the experience to stream all the entertainment you love! IMPROVEMENTS: General UX improvements throughout the app Improvements in app performance

Say hello to AT T TV NOW! The DIRECTV NOW you know is getting a new name. Same great features: Cloud DVR Beta no annual contract no installation. Same programming and content. Plus HBO included in PLUS and MAX packages! There s more! The DIRECTV NOW app name will be updated to AT T TV. To make things even easier the AT T TV and AT T TV NOW experiences are accessed from the same app for on the go viewing called AT T TV. This change will keep branding consistent and ignite customer excitement around the next generation of AT T TV products! Questions Answers Here! Do existing DIRECTV NOW customers have to do anything to get this new experience Existing DIRECTV NOW customers won t need to take any action and their service will continue as usual without interruption. Their application should automatically update upon release of the new name. AT T does recommend having their user name and password on hand in case of sign in issues. If automatic updates are not enabled on their device they will be directed to download the updated app when they login and they simply follow the onscreen instructions. They will be asked to re consent to the Terms and Conditions and Privacy Policy upon opening or post updating their app. The new app is called AT T TV. Is that the right app for customers Yes to make things even easier the AT T TV and AT T TV NOW experiences are accessed from the same app for on the go viewing called AT T TV. The customer s login credentials will determine what content appears and for current DIRECTV NOW customers their app will automatically update to the new AT T TV app. If automatic updates are not enabled on their device they will be directed to download the updated app when they login. What does the new AT T TV app icon look like The new AT T TV app icon is blue and features the AT T globe with TV in white. AT T TV App It will automatically update for anyone who has the current DIRECTV NOW app downloaded. If automatic updates are not enabled on their device they will be directed to download the updated app when they login. Do customers need to change anything for their third party apps such as HBO GO There will be no changes to any network apps customers are signed into. However if they sign out they will need to select AT T TV as their TV provider the next time they sign back in.

Added automatic starting of video playback when stream with mobile data setting is changed on iPad Changed to not show volume slider on iPhone video player Changed to un mute volume after receiving a phone call Fixed the placement of the closed caption popover after resuming from picture in picture on iPad Fixed watch from beginning on show details screen when launched from info button on video player Bug fixes and performance improvements

Improved dynamic updating of metadata on the video player after show transition on adjacent channels Improved audio volume setting to use system volume and in app mute instead of separate in app volume Improved the network screen to maintain the scroll position after selecting an item and adding to the watchlist Changed to display the series image as the background on the episode details screen Fixed to prevent scrubbing during AirPlay if content is configured to not allow it Fixed picture in picture to work properly on iPad after changing channel while viewing fullscreen video Fixed video player to automatically resume streaming live TV after accessing the Help Center on iPad

Added visual separator and gradient to Guide screen on iPhone iPad Increased size of favorite button on iPhone and iPad Guide screen to make it easier to tap Improved error handling to resume picture in picture on iPad after Internet connection disrupted Fixed audio playing after app is put into the background Fixed 1401 error while streaming after network connection is lost and then restarted Fixed occasional incorrect order of channels while swiping to change live channels

Improved error messaging Removed swipe to fast forward on shows that do not allow fast forwarding Fixed movie release year on Show Details screen Fixed picture in picture video playback for some on demand shows Fixed the show all button that was not being displayed for certain networks
Bug fixes and performance improvements

Added hint for swipe up gesture on Apple TV main screen Added ability to automatically play next on demand episode binge Added accessibility labels to Guide screen Improved picture in picture support for ABC and NBC channels on iPad Changed initial focus on Apple TV Guide screen to be on airing show instead of channel Improved removal of channels from Favorites Changed to use series image instead of episode image in Continue Watching row of Home screen Fixed display of Guide screen after rotation on iPhone Fixed audio playing after a phone call when app is in background

Added ability to swipe from first channel directly to the last channel and vice versa. Changed to display episode image instead of series image in the Continue Watching row on the Home screen. Improved support for picture in picture on iPad. Improved error message for QP1401 errors. Fixed QP1004006 error that occurs when resuming from the background on Apple TV. Fixed the positioning of the Extras button when it receives focus on Apple TV. Fixed the display of episode titles.
Performance Improvements

Added restart indicators on Guide screen for shows that are restartable Added ability to scrub backwards during live shows that are restartable Improved ability to move focus leftwards to all favorite channel button on Apple TV Guide screen no matter which row has focus Improved mute on launch to restore prior system volume upon exiting Improved the arrangement of buttons on the Show Detail screen for shows that are restartable Changed to remember last played channel after sign out sign in Changed to restart on demand show from beginning if it was previously watched to the end Fixed erroneous outside of U.S. condition Fixed erroneous too many concurrent streams condition Fixed loading of top shelf content on Apple TV after new install Fixed problem of video controls automatically hiding while scrubbing Fixed the display of lockout error message on Login screen Fixed occasional crash in ad player at startup
